ptmalloc3 is being used because of unsolved bugs in the glibc malloc
(as of Sep 24 2009)
The problem is a thread safety problem on multicore machines and is
architecture dependent.

Bug report
http://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=6952

RedHat Enterprise Linux fix
http://dcs.nac.uci.edu/support/sysadmin/security/archive/msg04994.html

ptmalloc3
http://www.malloc.de/en/

